com.twistral.toriamath.core.matrices

Class TMat3

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.twistral.toriamath.core.matrices.TMat3

  • public class TMat3
extends java.lang.Object
    A fast and mutable 3x3 double matrix class.
    All methods either return a numeric value or this matrix for method chaining purposes.
    Also see TMat2, TMat4, TMatN

      • invert

        public TMat3 invert()
        Calculates the inverse of this matrix and assigns it to this matrix.
        Simply does A = A-1.
        This method will return null if the matrix is not invertable (determinant is zero).
        Returns:
        this matrix for method chaining

      • flipHorizontally

        public TMat3 flipHorizontally()
        Flips this matrix horizontally.
        Example:
        [1 2 3] => [3 2 1]
        [4 5 6] => [6 5 4]
        [7 8 9] => [9 8 7]
        Returns:
        this matrix for method chaining

      • flipVertically

        public TMat3 flipVertically()
        Flips this matrix vertically.
        Example:
        [1 2 3] => [7 8 9]
        [4 5 6] => [4 5 6]
        [7 8 9] => [1 2 3]
        Returns:
        this matrix for method chaining
